node.text: The respiratory system of a Brazilian Skipper caterpillar in action. Their translucent skin makes this possible to see. As seen in the video, oxygen makes way to their tissues by the trachea. Air is pumped into the trachea, oxygen is taken in and carbon dioxide is pushed out #science #biology #caterpillar #anatomy #breathing (via science.feed)
